modules.description: This module provides functions for asynchronous serialization and writing of data using the Faraday buffer model. It supports operations like `serialize`, which writes data to a buffer and flushes it using a provided yield function, and `writev_of_fd`, which writes a list of bigstring iovecs to a file descriptor. It is used for efficient network or file I/O where data is generated incrementally and requires buffering before being sent or stored.
